cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper presents an approach for learning a visual representation from raw spatiotemporal signals in videos without supervision from semantic labels. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also uses a Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) for learning the representation, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions benchmark datasets like UCF101 and HMDB51, which are commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) research. Finally, the paper discusses pose estimation, which is a topic in neural networks (cs.NE).
